-- VW to raise up to 2 bln eur to fund complete Scania takeover
-- 
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 12:01PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, June 3 (Reuters) - Volkswagen <VOWG_p.DE> aims to raise up to 2 billion euros ($2.72 billion) by issuing new preference shares in an accelerated book building placement to institutional investors, it said on Tuesday.

The issue will help pay for VW's 6.7 billion euro takeover offer to shareholders of Swedish truckmaker Scania <SCVb.ST>, VW said in a statement. [ID:nWEB00NII]